This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it deals with referring expression grounding, which involves both visual and linguistic information. Additionally, the use of a knowledge extraction module suggests a potential application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The attention mechanisms and adaptive weighting scheme used in the proposed method also suggest a potential application of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the use of large-scale datasets suggests a potential application of multimedia (cs.MM) techniques.
